  • firstly, peel the skin of raw plantain.
  • slice them slightly thick. you can also slice them in round shapes.
  • soak them in water to prevent from browning.
  • meanwhile, prepare the besan batter by taking ¾ cup besan, 2 tbsp rice flour in a small mixing bowl.
  • also add ¼ tsp turmeric, ½ tsp chilli powder, pinch hing and ¾ tsp salt.
  • mix well making sure the spices are combined well.
  • further, add ½ cup water and whisk well.
  • prepare a smooth lump free batter.
  • now add ¼ tsp baking soda and mix gently.
  • pat dry the soaked plantain slices to remove excess moisture.
  • dip the sliced plantain slices into batter. coat with batter on both side.
  • slowly drop into hot oil and deep fry. stir occasionally.
  • fry until they become crisp and golden brown.
  • remove the pakodas and drain onto a paper towel.
  • finally, enjoy banana bajji with pudina chutney and masala chai.
